predictions.article: Impact of Recent Tariffs on U.S. Agriculture and Economy
predictions.prediction: U.S. agricultural exports, particularly soybeans, corn, and dairy, will decrease by at least 10% in the next quarter compared to the previous year.

predictions.article: Impact of Recent Tariffs on U.S. Agriculture and Economy
predictions.prediction: The USDA's forecasted agricultural trade deficit of $49 billion for 2025 will lead to policy interventions aimed at reducing the deficit, such as subsidies or new trade agreements, within the next three months.
